{
  "level": "Essential Grammar in Use",
  "part": "Unit 13",
  "tree": {
    "id": "root",
    "text": "Present perfect and past 1 | I have done and I did (现在完成时与一般过去时对比 1)",
    "emoji": "🕰️",
    "state": "emoji",
    "children": [
      {
        "id": "present_perfect_vs_past_simple",
        "text": "Core Difference (核心对比)",
        "emoji": "⚖️",
        "state": "hidden",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "present_perfect_now",
            "text": "Present perfect is a present tense -> tells us about the situation now (现在完成时是现在时态，用以阐述现在的情况)",
            "emoji": "📌",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "past_simple_past",
            "text": "Past simple tells us only about the past -> we don't know the situation now (一般过去时仅说明过去，不体现现在状况)",
            "emoji": "📜",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "recent_vs_non_recent",
        "text": "Recent vs Non-recent (新近与非新近事件)",
        "emoji": "⚡",
        "state": "hidden",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "recent_new",
            "text": "Use present perfect OR past simple for new/recent happenings (新近发生的事，可用现在完成时或一般过去时)",
            "emoji": "🆕",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "non_recent",
            "text": "Use past simple (NOT present perfect) for things that are not recent/new (非新近发生或历史事实，只能用一般过去时)",
            "emoji": "🏛️",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "conversation_transition",
        "text": "Conversation Flow (对话时态转换)",
        "emoji": "💬",
        "state": "hidden",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "give_new_info",
            "text": "Use present perfect to give new information (抛出新消息/话题时，先使用现在完成时)",
            "emoji": "📣",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "continue_talk",
            "text": "Use past simple when continuing to talk about details (继续深入探讨细节或过程时，转换成一般过去时)",
            "emoji": "🔍",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "key_examples",
        "text": "Key Examples (重点例句)",
        "emoji": "💡",
        "state": "hidden",
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "ex1",
            "text": "Tom has lost his key. (汤姆丢了钥匙——现在他进不去/没有钥匙)",
            "emoji": "🔑",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "ex2",
            "text": "Tom lost his key but now he has found it. (他丢过钥匙，但现在找到了——现在有钥匙)",
            "emoji": "😄",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "ex3",
            "text": "Mozart was a composer. He wrote more than 600 pieces of music. (莫扎特是作曲家，他写了600多首乐曲——历史事实)",
            "emoji": "🎼",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "ex4",
            "text": "Who invented the telephone? (谁发明了电话？——询问过去的事实)",
            "emoji": "📞",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "ex5",
            "text": "Ow! I've burnt myself. - How did you do that? - I picked up a hot dish. (时态转换对话示例)",
            "emoji": "🍽️",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "ex6",
            "text": "Somebody has spilt something on the sofa. - Well, it wasn't me. (有人把东西洒在沙发上了。- 额，那不是我。)",
            "emoji": "🛋️",
            "state": "hidden",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
